Class CustomerController

java.lang.Object
controller.CustomerController
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.fxml.Initializable
public class CustomerController extends Object implements javafx.fxml.Initializable
Class that contains event handlers, controller methods, and logical implementation for validation and creating / updating / deleting customers.

  • Method Details

    • initialize

      public void initialize(URL url, ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
      Initializes customer FXML file. Initializes values in combo boxes for country and division. If modifying a customer, loads appropriate values into text fields.
      Specified by:
      initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
      Parameters:
      url - Location of FXML file this controller controls behavior of, provided by FXMLLoader.
      resourceBundle - Used for localization and resource loading, provided by FXMLLoader.

    • onCountrySelectAction

      public void onCountrySelectAction()
      Handles the action when a country is selected in the country combo box. Retrieves and populates the division combo box based on the selected country.

    • onSaveAction

      void onSaveAction()
      Saves customer information entered in the form. If no customer is selected, will create a new record / row in database, and a new customer class object. If a customer is selected, will modify and update the information of the existing customer.

    • isValidCustomer

      boolean isValidCustomer()
      Checks if the customer information entered in the form is valid. Validates text fields and combo boxes for required information.
      Returns:
      true if customer information is valid, false otherwise.

    • onCancelAction

      void onCancelAction()
      Handles the action when the cancel button is pressed on the form. Shows a confirmation alert to the user, explaining that the entered information will not be saved. Changes the scene back to the home screen if the user confirms they want to cancel changes.

    • switchToHomeScene

      void switchToHomeScene() throws IOException
      Transitions the current scene back to the home scene. Loads "Home.fxml" using FXMLLoader as the scene for the primary stage.
      Throws:
      IOException - Occurs if there is a problem locating or loading the FXML file.
